{"type":"USJ","version":"3.1","content":[{"type":"book","marker":"id","content":["55-2TI-web.sfm English Arabic Names Version (EANV)"],"code":"2TI"},{"type":"para","marker":"ide","content":["UTF-8\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"h","content":["2 Timothy \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"toc1","content":["Paul’s Second Letter to Timothy \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"toc2","content":["2 Timothy \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"toc3","content":["2Ti \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"mt1","content":["Paul’s Second Letter to Timothy \n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"1","sid":"2TI 1"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"2TI 1:1"},"Paul, an apostle of Al Masih Isa through the will of Allah, according to the promise of the life which is in Masih Isa,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"2TI 1:2"},"to Timothy, my beloved child: Grace, mercy, and peace, from Allah the Father and Masih Isa our Lord.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"2TI 1:3"},"I thank Allah, whom I serve as my forefathers did, with a pure conscience. How unceasing is my memory of you in my\npetitions, night and day \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"2TI 1:4"},"longing to see you, remembering your tears, that I may be filled with joy;\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"2TI 1:5"},"having been reminded of the sincere faith that is in you, which lived first in your grandmother Lois, and your mother\nEunice, and, I am persuaded, in you also. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"2TI 1:6"},"For this cause, I remind you that you should stir up the gift of Allah which is in you through the laying on of my hands.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"2TI 1:7"},"For Allah didn’t give us a spirit of fear, but of power, love, and self-control.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"2TI 1:8"},"Therefore don’t be ashamed of the testimony of our Lord, nor of me his prisoner; but endure hardship for the Good News\naccording to the power of Allah, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"2TI 1:9"},"who saved us and called us with a holy calling, not according to our works, but according to his own purpose and grace,\nwhich was given to us in Masih Isa before times eternal, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"2TI 1:10"},"but has now been revealed by the appearing of our Saviour, Masih Isa, who abolished death, and brought life and\nimmortality to light through the Good News. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"2TI 1:11"},"For this I was appointed as a preacher, an apostle, and a teacher of the Gentiles.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"2TI 1:12"},"For this cause I also suffer these things. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Yet I am not ashamed, for I know him whom I have believed, and I am persuaded that he is able to guard that which I have\ncommitted to him against that day. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"2TI 1:13"},"Hold the pattern of sound words which you have heard from me, in faith and love which is in Masih Isa.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"2TI 1:14"},"That good thing which was committed to you, guard through the Holy Spirit who dwells in us.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"2TI 1:15"},"This you know, that all who are in Asia turned away from me, of whom are Phygelus and Hermogenes.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"2TI 1:16"},"May the Lord grant mercy to the house of Onesiphorus, for he often refreshed me, and was not ashamed of my chain,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"2TI 1:17"},"but when he was in Rome, he sought me diligently and found me\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18","sid":"2TI 1:18"},"(the Lord grant to him to find the Lord’s mercy in that day); and in how many things he served at Ephesus, you know very\nwell. \n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"2","sid":"2TI 2"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"2TI 2:1"},"You therefore, my child, be strengthened in the grace that is in Masih Isa.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"2TI 2:2"},"The things which you have heard from me amongst many witnesses, commit the same things to faithful men, who will be able\nto teach others also. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"2TI 2:3"},"You therefore must endure hardship as a good soldier of Masih Isa.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"2TI 2:4"},"No soldier on duty entangles himself in the affairs of life, that he may please him who enrolled him as a soldier.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"2TI 2:5"},"Also, if anyone competes in athletics, he isn’t crowned unless he has competed by the rules.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"2TI 2:6"},"The farmer who labours must be the first to get a share of the crops.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"2TI 2:7"},"Consider what I say, and may the Lord give you understanding in all things.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"2TI 2:8"},"Remember Al Masih Isa, risen from the dead, of the offspring",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[" \n",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["2:8 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["or, seed"]}],"caller":"+"}," of Dawood, according to my Good News, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"2TI 2:9"},"in which I suffer hardship to the point of chains as a criminal. But Allah’s word isn’t chained.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"2TI 2:10"},"Therefore I endure all things for the chosen ones’ sake, that they also may obtain the salvation which is in Masih Isa\nwith eternal glory. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"2TI 2:11"},"This saying is trustworthy: \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["“For if we died with him, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["we will also live with him. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"2TI 2:12"},"If we endure, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["we will also reign with him. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["If we deny him, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["he also will deny us. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"2TI 2:13"},"If we are faithless, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["he remains faithful; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["for he can’t deny himself.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"2TI 2:14"},"Remind them of these things, charging them in the sight of the Lord, that they don’t argue about words, to no profit, to\nthe subverting of those who hear. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"2TI 2:15"},"Give diligence to present yourself approved by Allah, a workman who doesn’t need to be ashamed, properly handling the\nWord of Truth. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"2TI 2:16"},"But shun empty chatter, for it will go further in ungodliness,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"2TI 2:17"},"and those words will consume like gangrene, of whom is Hymenaeus and Philetus:\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18","sid":"2TI 2:18"},"men who have erred concerning the truth, saying that the resurrection is already past, and overthrowing the faith of\nsome. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19","sid":"2TI 2:19"},"However Allah’s firm foundation stands, having this seal, “The Lord knows those who are\nhis,”",{"type":"note","marker":"x","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"xo","content":["2:19 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"xt","content":["Numbers 16:5"]}],"caller":"+"}," and, “Let every one who names the name of the\nLord",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["2:19 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["TR reads “Masih” instead of “the Lord”"]}],"caller":"+"}," depart from unrighteousness.”\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20","sid":"2TI 2:20"},"Now in a large house there are not only vessels of gold and of silver, but also of wood and of clay. Some are for honour,\nand some for dishonour. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21","sid":"2TI 2:21"},"If anyone therefore purges himself from these, he will be a vessel for honour, sanctified, and suitable for the master’s\nuse, prepared for every good work. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22","sid":"2TI 2:22"},"Flee from youthful lusts; but pursue righteousness, faith, love, and peace with those who call on the Lord out of a pure\nheart. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23","sid":"2TI 2:23"},"But refuse foolish and ignorant questionings, knowing that they generate strife.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24","sid":"2TI 2:24"},"The Lord’s servant must not quarrel, but be gentle towards all, able to teach, patient,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25","sid":"2TI 2:25"},"in gentleness correcting those who oppose him: perhaps Allah may give them repentance leading to a full knowledge of the\ntruth, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26","sid":"2TI 2:26"},"and they may recover themselves out of the Iblis’s snare, having been taken captive by him to his will.\n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"3","sid":"2TI 3"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"2TI 3:1"},"But know this: that in the last days, grievous times will come.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"2TI 3:2"},"For men will be lovers of self, lovers of money, boastful, arrogant, blasphemers, disobedient to parents, unthankful,\nunholy, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"2TI 3:3"},"without natural affection, unforgiving, slanderers, without self-control, fierce, not lovers of good,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"2TI 3:4"},"traitors, headstrong, conceited, lovers of pleasure rather than lovers of Allah,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"2TI 3:5"},"holding a form of godliness, but having denied its power. Turn away from these, also.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"2TI 3:6"},"For some of these are people who creep into houses and take captive gullible women loaded down with sins, led away by\nvarious lusts, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"2TI 3:7"},"always learning, and never able to come to the knowledge of the truth.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"2TI 3:8"},"Even as Jannes and Jambres opposed Musa, so these also oppose the truth, men corrupted in mind, who concerning the faith\nare rejected. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"2TI 3:9"},"But they will proceed no further. For their folly will be evident to all men, as theirs also came to be.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"2TI 3:10"},"But you followed my teaching, conduct, purpose, faith, patience, love, steadfastness,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"2TI 3:11"},"persecutions, and sufferings: those things that happened to me at Antioch, Iconium, and Lystra. I endured those\npersecutions. The Lord delivered me out of them all. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"2TI 3:12"},"Yes, and all who desire to live godly in Masih Isa will suffer persecution.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"2TI 3:13"},"But evil men and impostors will grow worse and worse, deceiving and being deceived.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"2TI 3:14"},"But you remain in the things which you have learnt and have been assured of, knowing from whom you have learnt them.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"2TI 3:15"},"From infancy, you have known the holy Scriptures which are able to make you wise for salvation through faith, which is in\nMasih Isa. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"2TI 3:16"},"Every Scripture is Allah-breathed and",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["3:16 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["or, Every writing inspired by Allah\nis"]}],"caller":"+"}," profitable for teaching, for reproof, for correction, and for instruction in righteousness,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"2TI 3:17"},"that each person who belongs to Allah may be complete, thoroughly equipped for every good work.\n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"4","sid":"2TI 4"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"2TI 4:1"},"I command you therefore before Allah and the Lord Al Masih Isa, who will judge the living and the dead at his appearing\nand his Kingdom: \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"2TI 4:2"},"preach the word; be urgent in season and out of season; reprove, rebuke, and exhort with all patience and teaching.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"2TI 4:3"},"For the time will come when they will not listen to the sound doctrine, but having itching ears, will heap up for\nthemselves teachers after their own lusts, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"2TI 4:4"},"and will turn away their ears from the truth, and turn away to fables.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"2TI 4:5"},"But you be sober in all things, suffer hardship, do the work of an evangelist, and fulfil your ministry.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"2TI 4:6"},"For I am already being offered, and the time of my departure has come.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"2TI 4:7"},"I have fought the good fight. I have finished the course. I have kept the faith.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"2TI 4:8"},"From now on, the crown of righteousness is stored up for me, which the Lord, the righteous judge, will give to me on that\nday; and not to me only, but also to all those who have loved his appearing.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"2TI 4:9"},"Be diligent to come to me soon, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"2TI 4:10"},"for Demas left me, having loved this present world, and went to Thessalonica; Crescens to Galatia; and Titus to Dalmatia.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"2TI 4:11"},"Only Luqa is with me. Take Marqus, and bring him with you, for he is useful to me for service.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"2TI 4:12"},"But I sent Tychicus to Ephesus. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"2TI 4:13"},"Bring the cloak that I left at Troas with Carpus when you come, and the books, especially the parchments.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"2TI 4:14"},"Alexander, the coppersmith, did much evil to me. The Lord will repay him according to his deeds,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"2TI 4:15"},"of whom you also must beware; for he greatly opposed our words.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"2TI 4:16"},"At my first defence, no one came to help me, but all left me. May it not be held against them.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"2TI 4:17"},"But the Lord stood by me and strengthened me, that through me the message might be fully proclaimed, and that all the\nGentiles might hear. So I was delivered out of the mouth of the lion.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18","sid":"2TI 4:18"},"And the Lord will deliver me from every evil work, and will preserve me for his heavenly Kingdom. To him be the glory\nforever and ever. Amen. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19","sid":"2TI 4:19"},"Greet Prisca and Aquila, and the house of Onesiphorus. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20","sid":"2TI 4:20"},"Erastus remained at Corinth, but I left Trophimus at Miletus sick.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21","sid":"2TI 4:21"},"Be diligent to come before winter. Eubulus salutes you, as do Pudens, Linus, Claudia, and all the brothers.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22","sid":"2TI 4:22"},"The Lord Al Masih Isa be with your spirit. Grace be with you. Amen.\n"]}]}